Blog Content Styling Improvement Plan

 Problem Analysis

 Root Cause:
 - BlogDetailPage.tsx:409 applies BOTH prose prose-lg (Tailwind Typography) AND .blog-content (custom CSS)
 - CSS conflicts: prose styles override .blog-content styles
 - Limited styling freedom: DOMPurify sanitization may strip custom styles
 - No per-post custom CSS support
 - Fixed brand colors/fonts with no author override

 User Requirements:
 - WordPress-level control (advanced layouts + full HTML/CSS freedom)
 - Fix all CSS issues: custom styles, fonts, layout, colors not working
 - Default to brand colors/fonts, allow per-post author customization

 ---
 Recommended Solution: Multi-Tier Styling System

 1. Remove CSS Conflicts ⚡ Priority

 File: frontend/src/pages/static/BlogDetailPage.tsx:409

 Change:
 // BEFORE (conflicting):
 <article className="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
   <div className="blog-content" dangerouslySetInnerHTML={...} />
 </article>

 // AFTER (conflict-free):
 <article className="mb-12">
   <div className="blog-content" dangerouslySetInnerHTML={...} />
 </article>

 Why: Removes Tailwind Typography interference, lets .blog-content control all styling.

