 4. DOMPurify Configuration 🔒

 File: frontend/src/pages/static/BlogDetailPage.tsx:413-419

 Enhanced whitelist:
 DOMPurify.sanitize(content, {
   ADD_ATTR: [
     'style', 'class', 'id', 'data-*',
     'width', 'height', 'colspan', 'rowspan',  // Tables
     'align', 'valign'  // Legacy support
   ],
   ADD_TAGS: ['iframe', 'svg', 'path', 'circle'],  // Media + icons
   ALLOWED_URI_REGEXP: /^(?:(?:https?|mailto|tel):|[^a-z]|[a-z+.-]+(?:[^a-z+.\-:]|$))/i,
   ALLOW_DATA_ATTR: true,
   ALLOW_UNKNOWN_PROTOCOLS: false,
   FORCE_BODY: false,  // Allow full HTML structures
   WHOLE_DOCUMENT: false,
   RETURN_DOM: false,
   RETURN_DOM_FRAGMENT: false
 })

 Note: Allows inline styles, classes, data attributes, SVGs, tables

