 Alternative Approaches

 Approach A: Keep Tailwind Typography (Not Recommended)

 - Customize prose in tailwind.config.js
 - Use prose-none to reset, then re-apply with .blog-content
 - Con: Less flexibility, harder to override per post

 Approach B: CSS-in-JS (Styled Components)

 - Replace CSS classes with styled components
 - Per-component scoping
 - Con: Larger bundle, runtime overhead, harder for authors to customize

 Approach C: Shadow DOM

 - Isolate blog content in Shadow DOM
 - Complete style isolation
 - Con: Complex, SEO issues, no style inheritance

